The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Arsenal open with 1-0 win
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Arsenal open with 1-0 win
                      
	London: Arsenal opened the Premier League season on Saturday with a 1-0 home win over newly promoted West Bromwich Albion.         
	Samir Nasri scored on his Premier League debut and, while the Gunners failed to add to their advantage, they never looked like surrendering it.         
	In the later matches, Bolton Wanderers beat promoted Stoke City 3-1 at the Reebok Stadium with first half goals from Gretar Steinsson, Kevin Davies and Johan Elmander, Boltons club record signing who scored on his debut.         
	Hull City marked their first match in the top division in their 104-year history with a 2-1 win over Fulham.         
	In other results, Middlesbrough beat Tottenham Hotspur 2-1, West Ham triumphed over Wigan with the same score and Blackburn won a thrilling encounter at Everton 3-2.         
	Liverpool also got off to a winning start, beating Sunderland 1-0 with a late goal from Fernando Torres. (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                          
